Pre-Game Insights: Netherlands are favourites but only just
This is a game neither team can afford to lose
Netherlands have a 6-5 T20I record against Nepal overall
Netherlands and Nepal have met three times earlier this year, in a triangular tournament in Kirtipur, and won once apiece in the league stage before Netherlands won a closely fought final
Miscellaneous Highlights: Dallas was where this World Cup got underway, and it got underway with a bang, as USA chased down 195 with 14 balls remaining. Twenty-one sixes were hit in that game, ten coming off the blade of Aaron Jones
Others: The question of Lalit Rajbanshi's spin partner becomes highly pertinent

Sagar Dhakal was one of only two Nepal bowlers to complete their four-over quota in their warm-up game against Canada. It suggests that Nepal may be mulling starting the 22-year-old against Netherlands, if they decide to go with two left-arm spinners
